(128, 'How can I set up my programme to display content fullscreen on external monitor', '    I want to build a programme that can render content on an external monitor, without having to manually drag a window across to the monitor and make it fullscreen.\r\n\r\nThink of a powerpoint-type application where you have a "controller" screen, and the "output" screen. The controller can send various different images to be drawn on the output screen.\r\n\r\nI want to build the application in Rust, but the language here is not important. I''m equally comfortable with C. What I really want to know is how to go about this, even what to search for. This is new terrain for me, and I don''t know where to start.\r\n\r\nThe only thing I know how to do is to create two windows, and drag one to the external monitor and press "fullscreen". How do applications such as ProPresenter, PowerPoint and Keynote automatically detect and render fullscreen content on external monitors/displays/projectors?\r\n\r\nI''m not too fussed on cross-system solutions here either, I''ll be working mainly with OSX.\r\n\r\nI realise that I''m not giving a whole lot of detail here, an I apologise. I just don''t know what the right terminology is to even begin searching for the solution. If someone could point me in the right direction that would be great, and much appreciated!\r\n\r\n     	', 40, 'PHP', 'CSS3', 'Symfony', '', '', 8, '2014-10-23 21:51:23', '2014-10-23 21:51:23'),
